messages: I'm a team player! I enjoy collaborating with others to create better outcomes together.
I enjoy working with others, but also appreciate working solo to accomplish my goals.
I work best on my own to accomplish my goals and find that others slow me down
I approach conflict head on and try to bring everyone onto the same page. When someone needs a mediator, they call me!
I work to resolve conflict if pushed, but avoid it if I can.
I prefer to keep to myself and avoid conflict.
I enjoy helping others to learn and develop.
I support others when needed, but don’t offer assistance without prompting.
I'm not really the mentoring type. I prefer to concentrate on myself and my own accomplishments.
I'm in tune with others and understand how they feel.
At times I understand others’ emotions, but sometimes I'm not sure how others feel.
Sometimes I struggle to understand how others feel.
I'm always trying to be the best I can be!
I set goals when needed, but don’t feel the need to always try to improve.
I feel comfortable with myself and don’t feel the need to constantly strive for more.
I enjoy change and can go with the flow with ease!
I can adapt when changes are needed, but also enjoy when things stay the same and I can get into a routine.
I'm not a fan of change, and prefer to stick with a steady routine.
I push through to accomplish my goals, no matter what life throws at me! I'm well-suited to work on long-term goals.
I see things through if I can, but sometimes a difficult situation leads me to change my goals.
Sometimes I prefer short-term goals and can be easily distracted.
I'm in touch with my thoughts and emotions.
I usually have a good handle on how I'm feeling and what’s going through my mind.
I find that I'm not really in touch with how I feel at times.
I recognize that a positive attitude brings success and happiness! I see the good first and am always looking toward the future.
I'm cautiously optimistic about the future.
I remember the past as some of the best times of my life, and am not sure if things will ever be that good again.
I'm as cool as a cucumber! I can control myself even in difficult times.
I find that I often can maintain my composure, but sometimes my emotions get the best of me.
I find that at times I'm impulsive and react before I consider the consequences.
Having high integrity is of great importance to me.
Most of the time, I present my best image.
I am not overly concerned with how I come across in my work and image.

I see the opportunity to motivate and engage others through establishing a shared vision for the future. I trust others and understand that people are motivated intrinsically and my job is to support and encourage them, and they will seek to accomplish shared goals.

I believe people need to be closely monitored and guided to succeed. I believe in the use of incentives to motivate others. I may be better suited to individual contributor than a leadership role, as I like to work independently.
